item.title: Want Rep?+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
item.dc:creator: @DrPepper DrPepper
item.description:
@DrPepper wrote:

OK well I used a netgar router…type in 192.168.1.1 and it should ask for a username and password

If you have no security its normally

Username: Admin
Password: Password

Sometimes their both admin…if thats not them then let me know.

On the left side scroll down to port forwarding/triggering…and click on it.

Click add custom service and then fill in this

Service Name [RSPS]
Service Type [TCP/UDP]
Starting Port [43594] (1~65534)
Ending Port [43594 (1~65534)
Server IP Address [192].[168].[1].[2]

the two might be a three try both.

Click apply and your done.
